<!--
  Component Object Reference: Connection (Connector Settings)
  API type attribute: connector-settings

  Stores environment-specific connection settings: URLs, credentials, SSL config.
  NOT PROMOTED — connections are pre-configured in prod by admins and mapped via
  ComponentMapping DataHub records.

  Source: Verified against actual GET /Component responses (2026-02-19)
  Confidence: HIGH

  Key structural points:
    - Inner XML element varies by connector type (NOT a single generic schema):
        HTTP Client: <HttpSettings> with typed attributes
        Database, SFTP, Disk, etc.: <GenericConnectorConfig> with <field id="..."> pairs
    - subType on Component wrapper: http, db, disk, sftp, ftp, etc.
    - <bns:encryptedValues> uses XPath to track which fields are encrypted
    - strip-env-config.groovy empties: password, host, url, port, EncryptedValue,
      apiKey, apiToken, secretKey, clientSecret, connectionString, jdbcUrl,
      privateKey, keystorePassword, proxyPassword (plus regex catch-all)

  IMPORTANT: This component type is NOT promoted. Admin-seeded ComponentMapping
  records map dev connection IDs → prod connection IDs.
-->

